        "title": "refactor: share QA runtime helpers",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Move shared QA markdown report rendering, live-lane artifact/error helpers, output tee, and Docker runtime helpers into the existing private local-only `openclaw/plugin-sdk/qa-runtime` seam.\n- Keep the public `openclaw/plugin-sdk/qa-runner-runtime` subpath focused on the existing QA runner discovery/loading contract, with no public SDK API baseline update.\n- Replace duplicated QA Lab and QA Matrix implementations with shared helper imports and thin Docker runtime adapters.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/check-plugin-sdk-subpath-exports.mjs`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/plugin-sdk/qa-runtime.test.ts src/plugin-sdk/qa-runner-runtime.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/qa-lab/src`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/qa-matrix/src`\n- `pnpm build`\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 <touched files>`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `node scripts/check-duplicates.mjs --coverage`\n- `node scripts/check-duplicates.mjs`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local`\n- After rebase onto `origin/main` at PR head `e988eeb76023`: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/plugin-sdk/qa-runtime.test.ts src/plugin-sdk/qa-runner-runtime.test.ts extensions/qa-lab/src extensions/qa-matrix/src` passed 96 files / 1001 tests.\n- Blacksmith Testbox via Crabbox `tbx_01ksp5c1rsj6q0b2hqh3s6dn2m`: `pnpm check:test-types` passed, then `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.agents-embedded-agent.config.ts --reporter=verbose` passed 75 files / 1231 tests. This rechecked the previously failing CI surfaces after pulling `main`.\n- Blacksmith Testbox via Crabbox `tbx_01ksp5k69g6jfmycq1rv81d79g`: `OPENCLAW_QA_MATRIX_NO_REPLY_WINDOW_MS=3000 pnpm openclaw qa matrix --provider-mode mock-openai --profile fast --fail-fast --output-dir .artifacts/qa-matrix-compat-rebase-mock` passed 15/15 scenarios. This exercised the shared Docker helper path in a real Matrix compose flow.\n\n## Real Behavior Proof\n\nBehavior addressed: QA Lab and QA Matrix now share report, live-lane artifact/error, output tee, and Docker runtime helper code instead of carrying duplicated implementations.\nReal environment tested: local Codex worktree on macOS with repo dependencies installed, plus Blacksmith Testbox through Crabbox for CI-parity type/test proof and a real Matrix Docker compose QA lane.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: the verification commands listed above were run after the final patch state; after pulling/rebasing on `origin/main`, the focused source tests, duplicate scan coverage/full duplicate scan, `check:test-types`, embedded-agent Vitest lane, and Matrix Docker QA lane were rerun or checked from the final PR branch state.\nEvidence after fix: focused private helper tests, QA Lab source tests, QA Matrix source tests, build, SDK subpath export check, duplicate scan coverage/full duplicate scan, scoped formatting, diff whitespace check, autoreview, CI-parity type/test lanes, and Matrix Docker compose QA passed. The first Testbox Matrix attempt used the default live-frontier provider and stopped before exercising the lane because the isolated environment had no portable OpenAI/Codex auth; it was rerun with `--provider-mode mock-openai` for deterministic Docker proof.\nObserved result after fix: existing QA Lab and Matrix tests continue passing while duplicate helper modules are removed or reduced to adapters, helper-only code stays on the private `qa-runtime` seam, the public SDK API baseline hash remains on the tracked main value, and the real Matrix Docker lane passes through the shared helper path.\nWhat was not tested: no credential-backed live transport run was executed.\n\n\n",
